### Generate a new pass
POST https://localhost:7000/Pass/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerName": "John Doe",
  "customerEmail": "john.doe@example.com",
  "points": 100,
  "barcodeMessage": "LOYALTY123456",
  "qrCodeData": "LOYALTY_ABC12345"
}

### Update points for existing pass
POST https://localhost:7000/Pass/update-points
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serialNumber": "your-serial-number-here",
  "points": 250,
  "deviceToken": "your-device-token-here"
}

### Get latest pass (called by Apple Wallet)
GET https://localhost:7000/Pass/passes/your-serial-number-here

### Register device for push notifications
POST https://localhost:7000/Pass/passes/your-serial-number-here/registrations/your-device-token-here

### Unregister device
DELETE https://localhost:7000/Pass/passes/your-serial-number-here/registrations/your-device-token-here

### Get pass log information
GET https://localhost:7000/Pass/passes/your-serial-number-here/log

### Example with actual data
POST https://localhost:7000/Pass/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerName": "Jane Smith",
  "customerEmail": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "points": 50
}

### Update points for Jane's pass (replace with actual serial number from above)
POST https://localhost:7000/Pass/update-points
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "serialNumber": "replace-with-actual-serial-number",
  "points": 150
}